Definition: or לְבֹנָה; from {{h3836}}; frankincense (from its whiteness or perhaps that of its smoke); (frank-) incense.
the same as {{h3828}}; Lebonah, a place in Palestine; Lebonah.
feminine of {{h3820}}; the heart; heart.
for {{h3852}}; flame; flame.

from {{h3823}}; used also like {{h3820}}; the heart (as the most interior organ); bethink themselves, breast, comfortably, courage, ((faint), (tender-) heart(-ed), midst, mind, × unawares, understanding.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3824}}; heart.
plural of {{h3833}}; lionesses; Lebaoth, a place in Palestine; Lebaoth. See also {{h1034}}.

a primitive root; properly, to be enclosed (as if with fat); by implication (as denominative from {{h3824}}); to unheart; i.e. (in a good sense) transport (with love), or (in a bad sense) stultify; to make cakes; make cakes, ravish, be wise.

a form of {{h3824}}; the heart; also used (figuratively) very widely for the feelings, the will and even the intellect; likewise for the centre of anything; care for, comfortably, consent, × considered, courag(-eous), friend(-ly), ((broken-), (hard-), (merry-), (stiff-), (stout-), double) heart(-ed), × heed, × I, kindly, midst, mind(-ed), × regard(-ed), × themselves, × unawares, understanding, × well, willingly, wisdom.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3820}}; heart.
from {{h3808}} and {{h7355}}; not pitied; Lo-Ruchamah, the symbolic name of a son of Hosea; Lo-ruhamah.
from {{h3808}} and {{h5971}} with pronominal suffix; not my people; Lo-Ammi, the symbolic name of a son of Hosea; Lo-ammi.
a primitive root; to muffle; cover.
from {{h3811}}; weary; Leah, a wife of Jacob; Leah.
a primitive root; to tire; (figuratively) to be (or make) disgusted; faint, grieve, lothe, (be, make) weary (selves).
or לוֹ דבַר; (Samuel 9:4,5), or לִדְבִר; (Joshua 13:26), (probably rather לֹדְבַר ); from {{h3808}} and {{h1699}}; pastureless; Lo-Debar, a place in Palestine; Debir, Lodebar.
plural of {{h3816}}; communities; Leummim, an Arabian; Leummim.
or לְאוֹם; from an unused root meaning to gather; a community; nation, people.
from the prepositional prefix and {{h410}}; (belonging) to God; Laël an Israelite; Lael.
from {{h3813}} (or perhaps for active participle of {{h3874}}); properly, muffled, i.e. silently; softly.
from the same as {{h3892}}; freshness, i.e. vigor; natural force.
from an unused root meaning to be new; fresh, i.e. unused or undried; green, moist.
from {{h3868}}; perverseness; perverse.
(Aramaic) from a root corresponding to {{h3867}}; properly, adhesion, i.e. (as preposition) with; × thee.
a primitive root; to lick; lick (up).
a form of {{h3895}}; Lechi, a place in Palestine; Lehi. Compare also {{h7437}}.
from an unused root meaning to be soft; the cheek (from its fleshiness); hence, the jaw-bone; cheek (bone), jaw (bone).
or לָחֻם; passive participle of {{h3898}}; properly, eaten, i.e. food; also flesh, i.e. body; while...is eating, flesh.
from {{h3898}}; See also {{h1036}}; food (for man or beast), especially bread, or grain (for making it); (shew-) bread, × eat, food, fruit, loaf, meat, victuals.
a primitive root; to feed on; figuratively, to consume; by implication, to battle (as destruction); devour, eat, × ever, fight(-ing), overcome, prevail, (make) war(-ring).
from {{h3803}}; properly, a circlet, i.e. a diadem; crown.
feminine active participle of {{h3803}}; the capital of a column; chapiter.
a primitive root; to butt or pound; bray.
a primitive root; to bruise or violently strike; beat (down, to pieces), break in pieces, crushed, destroy, discomfit, smite, stamp. l
or כֻּתֹּנֶת; from an unused root meaning to cover (compare {{h3802}}); a shirt; coat, garment, robe.

from an unused root meaning to clothe; the shoulder (proper, i.e. upper end of the arm; as being the spot where the garments hang); figuratively, side-piece or lateral projection of anything; arm, corner, shoulder(-piece), side, undersetter.

a primitive root; to enclose; hence (in a friendly sense) to crown, (in a hostile one) to besiege; also to wait (as restraining oneself); beset round, compass about, be crowned, inclose round, suffer.

or לוֹא; or לֹה; (Deuteronomy 3:11), a primitive particle; not (the simple or abs. negation); by implication, no; often used with other particles; × before,   or else, ere,   except, ig(-norant), much, less, nay, neither, never, no((-ne), -r, (-thing)), (× as though...,(can-), for) not (out of), of nought, otherwise, out of,   surely,   as truly as,   of a truth,   verily, for want,   whether, without.
(Aramaic) or לָה; (Aramaic) (Daniel 4:32), corresponding to {{h3808}}; or even, neither, no(-ne, -r), (can-) not, as nothing, without.
a primitive root; to knead; knead.
from {{h3888}}; kneading; Lush, a place in Palestine; Laish (from the margin). Compare {{h3919}}.
or לוּלֵי; from {{h3863}} and {{h3808}}; if not; except, had not, if (...not), unless, were it not that.

or לִין; a primitive root; to stop (usually over night); by implication, to stay permanently; hence (in a bad sense) to be obstinate (especially in words, to complain); abide (all night), continue, dwell, endure, grudge, be left, lie all night, (cause to) lodge (all night, in, -ing, this night), (make to) murmur, remain, tarry (all night, that night).
a primitive root; to gulp; figuratively, to be rash; swallow down (up).

a primitive root; properly, to make mouths at, i.e. to scoff; hence (from the effort to pronounce a foreign language) to interpret, or (generally) intercede; ambassador, have in derision, interpreter, make a mock, mocker, scorn(-er, -ful), teacher.
from {{h3867}}; something attached, i.e. a wreath; ornament.
or לֵוִי; patronymically from {{h3878}}; a Levite or descendant of Levi; Leviite.

from {{h3867}}; a wreathed animal, i.e. a serpent (especially the crocodile or some other large sea-monster); figuratively, the constellation of the dragon; also as a symbol of Babylon; leviathan, mourning.
from an unused root meaning to fold back; a spiral step; winding stair. Compare {{h3924}}.
or לֻחַ; from a primitive root; probably meaning to glisten; a tablet (as polished), of stone, wood or metal; board, plate, table.
probably from {{h3869}} (as growing there); Luz, the name of two places in Palestine; Luz.
active participle of {{h3907}}; (the) enchanter; Lochesh, an Israelite; Hallohesh, Haloshesh (includ. the article).
or לֻחוֹת; (Jeremiah 48:5), from the same as {{h3871}}; floored; Luchith, a place East of the Jordan; Luhith.
from {{h3874}}; a veil; covering.
a primitive root; to wrap up; cast, wrap.
from {{h3875}}; covering; Lotan, an Idumaean; Lotan.
the same as {{h3875}}; Lot, Abraham's nephew; Lot.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3880}}; Levite.
from {{h3867}}; attached; Levi, a son of Jacob; Levi. See also {{h3879}}, {{h3881}}.
probably from an unused root meaning to gather; an assembly; company.
or לֻא; or לוּ; a conditional particle; if; by implication (interj. as a wish) would that!; if (haply), peradventure, I pray thee, though, I would, would God (that).
from the prepositional prefix meaning to or for and {{h2005}}; properly for if; hence, therefore; for them (by mistake for prepositional suffix).
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3860}}; therefore; also except; but, except, save, therefore, wherefore.
or לוּדִיִּי; patrial from {{h3865}}; a Ludite or inhabitants of Lud (only in plural); Ludim. Lydians.
a primitive root; properly, to twine, i.e. (by implication) to unite, to remain; also to borrow (as a form of obligation) or (caus.) to lend; abide with, borrow(-er), cleave, join (self), lend(-er).

or לֻבִּי; (Daniel 11:43), partrial from a name probably derived from an unused root meaning to thirst, i.e. a dry region; apparently; a Libyan or inhabitant of interior Africa (only in plural); Lubim(-s), Libyans.
probably of foreign derivation; Lud, the name of two nations; Lud, Lydia.
a primitive root; (compare {{h3867}}, {{h3874}} and {{h3885}}); to turn aside , i.e. (literally) to depart, (figuratively) be perverse; depart, froward, perverse(-ness).
probably of foreign origin; some kind of nut-tree, perhaps the almond; hazel.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3899}}; feast.
a primitive root; properly, to burn in, i.e. (figuratively) to rankle; wound.
from {{h3857}}; a blaze; also (from the idea of enwrapping) magic (as covert); flaming, enchantment.
a primitive root; properly, to lick, i.e. (by implication) to blaze; burn (up), set on fire, flaming, kindle.
a primitive root meaning properly, to burn, i.e. (by implication); to be rabid (figuratively, insane); also (from the exhaustion of frenzy) to languish; faint, mad.
from an unused root meaning to glow (compare {{h3851}}) or else to be earnest (compare {{h3854}}); Lahad, an Israelite; Lahad.
from an unused root meaning to be eager; intense mental application; study.
plural of {{h3851}}; flames; Lehabim, a son of Mizraim, and his descendants; Lehabim.
or לַהֶבֶת; feminine of {{h3851}}, and meaning the same; flame(-ming), head (of a spear).
from an usused root meaning to gleam; a flash; figuratively, a sharply polished blade or point of a weapon; blade, bright, flame, glittering.
from an unused root of uncertain signification; Lod, a place in Palestine; Lod.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3847}}; clothe.
from an unused root apparently meaning to deepen or hollow (like {{h3537}}); a log or measure for liquids; log (of oil).
from {{h3835}}; properly, whiteness, i.e. (by implication) transparency; paved.
the same as {{h3839}}; Libnah, a place in the Desert and one in Palestine; Libnah.
from {{h3835}}; properly, (the) white, i.e. the moon; moon. See also {{h3838}}.
from {{h3835}}; a brick (from the whiteness of the clay); (altar of) brick, tile.
from {{h3825}}; (the) white mountain (from its snow); Lebanon, a mountain range in Palestine; Lebanon.
from {{h3835}}; white; Libni, an Israelite; Libni.
patronymically from {{h3845}}; a Libnite or descendants of Libni (collectively); Libnites.

or לָבֵשׁ; a primitive root; properly, wrap around, i.e. (by implication) to put on a garment or clothe (oneself, or another), literally or figuratively; (in) apparel, arm, array (self), clothe (self), come upon, put (on, upon), wear.
from {{h3835}}; some sort of whitish tree, perhaps the storax; poplar.
or לְבָנָה; the same as {{h3842}}; Lebana or Lebanah, one of the Nethinim; Lebana, Lebanah.
a primitive root; also as denominative from {{h3843}}; to be (or become) white; to make bricks; make brick, be (made, make) white(-r).
or rather לְבִבָה; from {{h3823}} in its original sense of fatness (or perhaps of folding); a cake (either as fried or turned); cake.
the same as {{h3836}}; Laban, a Mesopotamian; also a place in the Desert; Laban.
or (Genesis 49:12) לָבֵן; from {{h3835}}; white; white.
(Aramaic) corresponding to {{h3830}}; garment.
or לְבֻשׁ; from {{h3847}}; a garment (literally or figuratively); by implication (euphemistically) a wife; apparel, clothed with, clothing, garment, raiment, vestment, vesture.

or (Ezekiel 19:2) לְבִיָּא; irregular masculine plural לְבָאִים; irregular feminine plural לְבָאוֹת; from an unused root meaning to roar; compare {{h738}}; a lion (properly, a lioness as the fiercer (although not a roarer;)); (great, old, stout) lion, lioness, young (lion).
a primitive root; to overthrow; intransposed, to fall; fall.
